    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-11T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-11T15:00:00-05:00" n="576"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/391: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-11T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 11, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Your despatch 470, May 5.<note n="26" xml:id="d576fn26">Not printed, but see
                        telegram No. 31, May 5, 4 p.m., <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Notice
                    given by Foreign Minister does not indicate what schedule products it is desired
                    to restrict, extent of restriction in each case, or share of each global quota
                    intended to be allotted to the United States.</p>
                <pb facs="0624" n="616" xml:id="pg_616"/>
                <p>You should secure specific proposals from Tobar on above questions and transmit
                    substance thereof by telegram, keeping in mind provisions of second paragraph of
                    Article VII regarding 30 day period within which agreement should be
                    reached.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
